description:
Networks of Power

Sociopolitical Documentary hosted by Christopher Meyer, published by BSkyB in 2012 - English narration. 
http://docuwiki.net/images/d/db/Networks-of-Power-Cover.jpg

Information
------------------------------
Former diplomat Sir Christopher Meyer explores the world's most influential cities.

1)  Mumbai 
He meets a film icon and learns about the city's secretive diamond network.

2)  Moscow 
He discovers how the Russian capital has changed since the fall of the Iron Curtain.

3)  New York City 
He meets billionaire mayor Michael Bloomberg and discovers what drives the iconic city.

4)  Rome 
He discovers how the Eternal City is reshaping in the aftermath of the Berlusconi government.

5)  Los Angeles 
He discovers a changing movie industry and a sprawling city with a darker side away from the glamour of Hollywood.

6)  London 
He discovers the modern make-up of London, meeting MP Louise Mensch, mayor Boris Johnson and newspaper magnate Evgeny Lebedev.
